OL,5, Average pay growth rose above inflation
OL,6, for the first time in almost two years,
OL,7, in a sign that the squeeze on living   
OL,8, costs may be starting to ease.         
OL,10,FWages rose at an annual rate of 7.8%   
OL,11,Fbetween June and August, figures show. 
OL,13,FThat was higher than average inflation 
OL,14,Fover the same three months, which      
OL,15,Fmeasures the rate at which prices rise.
OL,17,FRevised figures showed pay overtook    
OL,18,Finflation in the three months to July, 
OL,19,Fmeaning wages are outpacing prices for 
OL,20,Fthe first time since October 2021.     
